First of all, there is the starting idea: each event must be treated as a separate case, with its particular needs and requirements, and must be offered original and personalized services. 
The perfect event conveys, even in its smallest details, the chosen mood and atmosphere to the guests: to do so, 
you must not put any limit in the services offered to the customers, giving the event an absolutely personal mark.

Second, a constant budget control allows to rationalize and allocate costs in the best way at each stage of the organization of the event.
